description:
Reported 2026-05-16: after Slider C (4crg) shipped, clicking a slider's next/prev arrow was moving ALL initialized sliders on the page in lockstep, not just the slider being clicked.

Root cause: in scripts/collection-slider.js (bundled into custom-theme.js around line 8901), the original navigation config passed CSS selector strings:

  navigation: {
    nextEl: '.navigator-box .swiper-button-next',
    prevEl: '.navigator-box .swiper-button-prev'
  }

Swiper internally does document.querySelectorAll(selector) and binds click handlers to ALL matching elements. Since every collection-slider has its own .navigator-box .swiper-button-next, every Swiper instance was binding to every navigator-box on the page.

Bug was latent in original code, masked by sequential one-at-a-time init pre-Fix-B (rootMargin 200px + pre-init height 1185px meant only one slider was ever initialized at a time). Fix B's batch init (rootMargin 1200px) exposed it because multiple sliders now initialize in the same scroll event.

Fix shipped same day: pass DOM element references scoped to each slider's .wrapper parent.

  var sliderWrapper = el.closest('.wrapper');
  var navNextEl = sliderWrapper.querySelector('.navigator-box .swiper-button-next');
  var navPrevEl = sliderWrapper.querySelector('.navigator-box .swiper-button-prev');
  ...
  navigation: { nextEl: navNextEl, prevEl: navPrevEl }

Verified on draft theme 140785582179: with 3 sliders initialized (idx 4, 5, 6), clicking one arrow moved only idx=5 (-178.667px); others stayed at translate3d(0,0,0). Pre-fix would have moved all three.

Pushed to live theme 131664707683 same day.

design:
Implementation approach: extend the existing createElement override
pattern from layout/theme.liquid (used for VQB/BTA gating, commits
cc8d92d + ed3d161). Add a new <link>-intercept guard that runs BEFORE
{{ content_for_header }} so it intercepts Pro Blogger's asset
injection at parse time.

Two interception mechanisms run in tandem:

1. document.createElement override
   When Pro Blogger (or any app) calls document.createElement('link')
   and then sets el.href = '...problogger.css...', the setter fires
   our intercept. We rewrite the attributes BEFORE the link is
   inserted into <head>:
     - Save the original href
     - Set rel='preload', as='style', media='print' (forces non-render-
       blocking fetch)
     - Add an onload handler that re-sets rel='stylesheet', media='all'
       after the load completes — applying the CSS asynchronously.
   This catches dynamic <link> injection.

2. MutationObserver fallback (synchronous)
   Watch document.head for childList mutations. Any <link
   rel="stylesheet"> that matches BLOCKED_ASSETS patterns and was
   added during HTML parse (not via createElement) gets the same
   rewrite applied as soon as it's inserted.
   This catches HTML-parser-inserted <link> from content_for_header.

BLOCKED_ASSETS patterns (high-confidence; from OC audit):
  - 'problogger.css' (Pro Blogger's own CSS)
  - 'owl.carousel'   (Owl Carousel — matches both owl.carousel.min.css
                      and any future versioned variants)
  - 'pro-blogger'    (extra safety match for app extension CDN paths)

Implementation outline (~60-80 LoC in layout/theme.liquid, placed
BEFORE {{ content_for_header }} on the same line/block where the
VQB/BTA guard lives):

```liquid
{%- comment -%}
  Pro Blogger interim CSS defer (bd 01vl.2, 2026-05-16). Intercepts
  problogger.css + owl.carousel.min.css <link rel=stylesheet>
  insertions and swaps them to media=print + onload rel=stylesheet
  pattern, removing Pro Blogger from the LCP critical path. INTERIM
  until Vertex AI replacement (bd oyw + 01vl.3 Vertex wiring) lands;
  remove this guard at that time.
{%- endcomment -%}
<script>
(function() {
  var BLOCKED_ASSETS = ['problogger.css', 'owl.carousel', 'pro-blogger'];
  var matches = function(href) {
    if (typeof href !== 'string') return false;
    for (var i = 0; i < BLOCKED_ASSETS.length; i++) {
      if (href.indexOf(BLOCKED_ASSETS[i]) !== -1) return true;
    }
    return false;
  };
  var deferLink = function(el) {
    if (el.tagName !== 'LINK') return;
    if (el.rel !== 'stylesheet') return;
    if (!matches(el.href)) return;
    // Convert to non-blocking load pattern (matches our theme.css pattern)
    el.media = 'print';
    el.onload = function() {
      this.media = 'all';
      this.onload = null;
    };
  };

  // 1. createElement override — catches dynamic createElement('link') paths
  var _createElement = document.createElement.bind(document);
  document.createElement = function(tag) {
    var el = _createElement.apply(document, arguments);
    if (typeof tag === 'string' && tag.toLowerCase() === 'link') {
      // Intercept href setter so we modify BEFORE insertion
      var _setHref = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(HTMLLinkElement.prototype, 'href').set;
      Object.defineProperty(el, 'href', {
        configurable: true,
        get: function() {
          return Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(HTMLLinkElement.prototype, 'href').get.call(this);
        },
        set: function(v) {
          _setHref.call(this, v);
          deferLink(this);
        }
      });
    }
    return el;
  };

  // 2. MutationObserver fallback — catches HTML-parser-inserted <link>
  //    from content_for_header (Pro Blogger app embed)
  var observer = new MutationObserver(function(mutations) {
    mutations.forEach(function(m) {
      m.addedNodes.forEach(function(node) {
        if (node.tagName === 'LINK') deferLink(node);
      });
    });
  });
  observer.observe(document.documentElement, { childList: true, subtree: true });
})();
</script>
```

Placement: in <head> BEFORE {{ content_for_header }}, but AFTER the
existing VQB/BTA guard. The two guards share the same createElement-
override + MutationObserver pattern but operate on different element
types (VQB/BTA = scripts; this = links).

Edge cases handled:
- href is a relative URL → indexOf check still works
- href changes after assignment (rare) → setter fires again
- <link> with no href → matches() returns false, no rewrite
- <link rel="preload"> already → rel !== 'stylesheet', skipped
- <noscript> fallback for Pro Blogger CSS → noscript blocks execute
  only without JS; the JS-disabled fallback is acceptable

Hard rules:
- Coordinator (CC) owns the live push. Manual visual smoke on top-5
  article pages required pre-live.
- Phase 2 acceptance includes: Pro Blogger widgets still render
  visually (carousels show), pagination/click works, no JS errors
  in console.
- Rollback path: empty the BLOCKED_ASSETS array (1-line revert).
- Do NOT block JS payloads in this phase — Phase 2b (separate ticket)
  if needed later.
- Do NOT touch the article-template hero-block setting in admin —
  that's separate from this fix.

Smoke test plan:
1. python3 scripts/check-overlay-css.py → 0 kt0 violations.
2. shopify theme push --theme=140785582179 --nodelete --only=layout/theme.liquid.
3. Visit each of these on draft preview, verify carousels render:
   /blogs/hair-education/salon-hair-color-vs-box-dye-...
   /blogs/hair-education/before-and-after-the-transformative-power-of-purple-shampoo
   /blogs/hair-education/purple-vs-blue-shampoo-philippines
   /blogs/hair-education/an-ultimate-guide-to-anti-dandruff-shampoos-in-the-philippines
   /blogs/hair-education/understanding-sodium-lauryl-sulfate-in-shampoos-risks
4. DevTools Network tab: confirm problogger.css fetches with
   Priority=Lowest (non-render-blocking). owl.carousel.min.css same.
5. Lighthouse on the top-1 page: 'Eliminate render-blocking resources'
   should no longer flag problogger.css or owl.carousel.
6. Click into the related-products carousel: items load + click works.
7. Click into the related-articles carousel: items load + click works.
8. Test on at least 5 collection templates (per OC audit, 7 collection
   templates use Pro Blogger blocks): confirm widgets render there too.

If any of (3)-(8) fails: rollback (set BLOCKED_ASSETS = []) and re-investigate.

Phase 2 → Phase 3 transition:
- Phase 3 (Vertex AI wiring) starts when bd oyw enters its
  implementation window AND has product/article recommendation
  endpoints ready for theme integration.
- At that point: build the Vertex widgets first (non-disruptive
  alongside Pro Blogger), measure, then disable Pro Blogger blocks
  in admin and remove this intercept code in one commit.

description:
Build the JS module that wires the modal form to Klaviyo's public Back-in-Stock Subscription API.

NEW FILES (both required per house dev/min mirror rule):
- assets/notify-when-available.dev.js (~250 LoC, readable)
- assets/notify-when-available.js (minified mirror)

LOADED FROM: layout/theme.liquid via <script src="{{ 'notify-when-available.js' | asset_url }}" defer></script>.

MODULE BEHAVIOR:
1. Bind every [data-notify-trigger] to open the modal (via Micromodal.show('notify-when-available-modal')).
2. On open, populate modal subtitle with data-product-title + data-variant-title.
3. On submit:
   - Validate: email via HTML5; PH phone via /^9\d{9}$/ (10 local digits) and prepend "+63" for E.164.
   - POST to https://a.klaviyo.com/client/back-in-stock-subscriptions/?company_id=<PUBLIC_KEY> with revision header "2024-10-15" and payload:
     {
       "data": {
         "type": "back-in-stock-subscription",
         "attributes": {
           "profile": { "email": "<email>" }  // OR "phone_number": "+63XXXXXXXXXX"
           },
           "channels": ["EMAIL"]  // OR ["SMS"]
         },
         "relationships": {
           "variant": {
             "data": { "type": "catalog-variant", "id": "$shopify:::$default:::<variant_id>" }
           }
         }
       }
     }
4. PATCH /client/profiles/ to set custom property bis_channel_preference = "email" | "sms" (for Klaviyo flow branching).
5. If newsletter checkbox checked: POST to /client/subscriptions/ for the newsletter list (consent timestamp = now).
6. On success: show inline confirmation in modal, close after 2s.
7. On error: surface specific message; do NOT close modal; allow retry.
8. Fire klaviyoForms-style custom event so GA4 listeners in layout/theme.liquid:164-170 see the conversion.

PUBLIC KEY SOURCE: read from <meta name="klaviyo-company-id" content="..."> or theme settings (coordinate with T1 owner).

OWNER: OC via /offload. If LoC exceeds 120 after factoring in error handling, decompose into T4a (dev.js) + T4b (minify + parity) per free-tier scope discipline (even on paid tier, smaller increments are easier to QA).

Parent: hairmnl-theme-987 (desktop CLS p75 0.20, 44% good)

odv investigation (2026-05-12) identified Judge.me as the highest-impact #MainContent CLS source.

Problem: Judge.me JS hydrates after first paint. Two elements shift:
1. PDP: `#judgeme_product_reviews` — large block below product description that expands when JS adds star ratings + review HTML
2. Collection/home: `.jdgm-prev-badge` (preview badge below product title in grid cards) and `.jdgm-widget.jdgm-preview-widget` — expands from hidden → visible

Fix: reserve vertical space via min-height so hydration doesn't shift surrounding content.

Known pattern: snippets/judgeme_widgets.liquid uses `.jdgm-hidden` → visible pattern already documented in css-overrides.liquid.

### Files to modify
- assets/custom-theme.css (append at end of file, same pattern as xn4 + jvf)

### What to add

#### Selector group 1 — PDP review block
```css
/* ── CLS fix 2026-05-12 hairmnl-theme-BDID (987 Phase 2 — Judge.me review block) ── */
body.template-product #judgeme_product_reviews {
  min-height: 220px;
}
body.template-product .jdgm-widget.jdgm-review-widget {
  min-height: 220px;
}
```
220px = approximate height of star summary row + first review card before full hydration. Adjust if audit shows a different real height.

#### Selector group 2 — Preview badges on collection/home grid cards
```css
body.template-collection .jdgm-prev-badge,
body.template-index .jdgm-prev-badge {
  min-height: 18px;
  display: block;
}
```
18px = one line of star text. Badge is inline by default; `display:block` prevents zero-height collapse before hydration.

### Hard constraints (mandatory — regression lesson from xn4 2026-05-12)
- ALL selectors MUST be prefixed with body.template-* scope.
- NO contain:layout|paint|strict|content, transform, filter, backdrop-filter, perspective, will-change:transform, will-change:filter on any selector. These create containing blocks for fixed overlays (kt0 lesson). Judge.me DOM lives inside #MainContent which has fixed overlay siblings.
- CSS only. No JS changes.
- Only stage assets/custom-theme.css.
- No shopify theme push. No git push. No bd close.

design:
## CSS-only fix in snippets/css-overrides.liquid

Add (after the existing blog .rte img rule at line 138-143):

```css
/* CLS fix YYYY-MM-DD <bd-id> — Pro Blogger related-articles thumbnails.
   snippets/pro-blogger.snippet.related-item.liquid renders <img> without
   width/height attrs (lines 5 + 20); image URLs use Shopify CDN
   ?height=400 query param so they're 400px tall but variable width.
   Without dimensions, each thumbnail shifts content as it loads —
   6+ thumbnails per blog post = CLS 0.52 on
   hair-education/purple-vs-blue-shampoo-philippines (POOR bucket, GSC
   5/10). Existing article-content-with-img-dims snippet doesn't
   recognize ?height= query params, only _WxH.ext patterns.

   Reserve 1:1 aspect-ratio (matches typical thumbnail container style
   per .pb_image_wrapper) so browser allocates space before image loads.
   width:100% lets the image fill its parent. height:auto + object-fit:
   cover preserves visual fit when actual image aspect differs from 1:1.
   background reserves a visible placeholder color during load. */
.pb_image_wrapper img:not([width]):not([height]) {
  aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  display: block;
  background: #f4f6f8;
  object-fit: cover;
}

/* Same pattern for .responsive-wide-image which also renders unsized
   in some article contexts (cross-post-blogs widget). 16:9 fallback
   matches the existing .blog__article__content rule at line 138-143. */
.responsive-wide-image:not([width]):not([height]) {
  aspect-ratio: auto 16 / 9;
  width: 100%;
  height: auto;
  display: block;
  background: #f4f6f8;
}
```

Files: snippets/css-overrides.liquid (CSS-only, ~30 lines).

Match existing CLS-fix comment convention: `/* CLS fix YYYY-MM-DD <bd-id> — <reason> */`.

Optional follow-up (not in this scope): edit pro-blogger.snippet.related-item.liquid lines 5 + 20 to add explicit `width="400" height="400" loading="lazy" decoding="async"` attributes to the <img> tags. CSS-only fix is sufficient for CLS but Liquid edit also helps the browser preconnect/prioritize correctly. Filed as a P3 follow-up if/when this surfaces in GSC again.

## File: scripts/build-perf-dashboard.py

### Depends on
Child 1 (aqe) MUST be merged into the working tree first. CHART_DATA is now `{"mobile": {...}, "desktop": {...}}` after that change.

### Current state (around line 1170-1196)
```js
